items.title: Can Cory Doctorow’s Book ‘Enshittification’ Change the Tech Debate?
items.description: Cory Doctorow’s new book looks to offer comfort, and solutions, to the inescapable feeling that digital platforms have gotten worse.

items.title: French Prime Minister Sébastien Lecornu Resigns
items.description: Sébastien Lecornu’s departure ratcheted up pressure on President Emmanuel Macron to call snap parliamentary elections.

items.title: How Bari Weiss of The Free Press Won the Top Job at CBS News
items.description: At The Free Press, she battled “wokeness” and buddied up with billionaires. Now she’s the editor in chief of CBS News.

items.title: Paramount Buys Bari Weiss’s Free Press, Starting a New Era at CBS News
items.description: Bari Weiss, a founder of The Free Press, will become editor in chief of CBS News.

items.title: OpenAI Agrees to Use Computer Chips From AMD
items.description: Weeks after a $100 billion agreement to use computer chips from Nvidia, OpenAI has signed a similar deal with a rival chipmaker.
